leadership_approach|results_process_vision_people|concentrated|results|process|vision|people|Recognised for Results-first leadership|This pattern shows up in how you notice drift, slow decisions, or unclear ownership before anything else. Others experience clear priorities, practical movement, and a stronger sense of what happens next.|At its best, Results gives people clear priorities, practical movement, and a stronger sense of what happens next. It narrows when Results alone is not enough, so bring Process, Vision, or People in earlier when the situation needs stronger structure, coordination, and repeatability, longer-range direction, future context, and wider meaning, or deeper trust, communication, and shared confidence.|active|leadership_approach::results_process_vision_people::concentrated
leadership_approach|results_process_vision_people|paired|results|process|vision|people|Recognised for Results and Process working together|This pattern shows up in how you combine deciding what needs to happen with organising the work into structure and sequence. Others experience clear priorities, practical movement, and a stronger sense of what happens next alongside clearer coordination, reliable follow-through, and a path others can use.|At its best, Results and Process help leadership handle clearer outcomes, decisions, and next steps and stronger structure, coordination, and repeatability. It narrows when the pair runs ahead of Vision or People, so bring them in earlier when the situation needs longer-range direction, future context, and wider meaning or deeper trust, communication, and shared confidence.|active|leadership_approach::results_process_vision_people::paired
leadership_approach|results_process_vision_people|graduated|results|process|vision|people|Recognised for a Results-led leadership sequence|This pattern shows up in how your leadership moves from Results through Process, Vision, and People in a clear order. Others experience clear priorities, practical movement, and a stronger sense of what happens next, with each later signal adding range as the work broadens.|At its best, this sequence gives your leadership a natural order of attention. It narrows when the later signals arrive too late, so bring Vision and People in before the work closes around the first route.|active|leadership_approach::results_process_vision_people::graduated
leadership_approach|results_process_vision_people|balanced|results|process|vision|people|Recognised for flexible Results-led range|This pattern shows up in how you move between Results, Process, Vision, and People without relying on one route for every situation. Others experience leadership with several usable routes, especially when you name which route matters now.|At its best, this gives your leadership several usable routes into the work. It narrows when switching routes creates confusion, so name the current priority before moving to the next signal.|active|leadership_approach::results_process_vision_people::balanced
